### ====================================================================
### POSITIVE SCENARIOS (HAPPY PATH)
### ====================================================================

### 1. Create a brand new employee with full FIO (including Middle Name)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mr.",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "firstName": "John",
  "middleName": "Edward",
  "email": "john.smith@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 2. Create an employee WITHOUT a Middle Name (e.g., foreign citizen)
### This should succeed because middleName is not annotated with @NotBlank
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Ms.",
  "lastName": "Blunt",
  "firstName": "Emily",
  "middleName": null,
  "email": "emily.blunt@example.com",
  "phone": "+1987654321"
}

### 3. Create a person with the SAME First and Last name, but a DIFFERENT Middle Name
### This should succeed! (John Edward Smith vs John Peterson Smith)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mr.",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "firstName": "John",
  "middleName": "Peterson",
  "email": "john.peterson@example.com",
  "phone": "+1555666777"
}


### ====================================================================
### BUSINESS LOGIC VALIDATION (DB UNIQUE CONSTRAINTS)
### ====================================================================

### 4. Duplicate Email Check (Should fail with 409 Conflict)
### Uses an existing email (john.smith@example.com) but completely different FIO
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Dr.",
  "lastName": "Watson",
  "firstName": "Emma",
  "middleName": "Grace",
  "email": "john.smith@example.com",
  "phone": "+111222333"
}

### 5. Duplicate FIO Check (Should fail with 409 Conflict)
### Uses an existing full name (Smith John Edward) but a completely fresh email
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Prof.",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "firstName": "John",
  "middleName": "Edward",
  "email": "fresh.email@example.com",
  "phone": "+444555666"
}


### ====================================================================
### INPUT VALIDATION (jakarta.validation / DTO Constraints)
### ====================================================================

### 6. Missing Title (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "middleName": "Mary",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+777888999"
}

### 7. Missing Mandatory Names (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mr.",
  "lastName": "",
  "firstName": "   ",
  "middleName": "ValidMiddle",
  "email": "validation.test@example.com",
  "phone": "+123"
}

### 8. Invalid Email Format (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mr.",
  "lastName": "Simpson",
  "firstName": "Homer",
  "middleName": "Jay",
  "email": "homer.simpson_at_domain.com",
  "phone": "+555333"
}

### 9. Empty Email (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mr.",
  "lastName": "Simpson",
  "firstName": "Homer",
  "middleName": "Jay",
  "email": "",
  "phone": "+555333"
}